<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
<a class="spoiler" href="/questions/735796-what-is-the-deal-with-the-gray-creature">This question contains spoilers...</a>
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[What is the deal with the "gray creature"? It's heavily implied that it's the mass of bones bound together by gray scraps of cloth, but if so and the gray creature is a zombie or something, that is the only thing in the book that would be supernatural. Everything else can be explained away by drugs, brainwashing, hypnosis, etc. If we assume this is historical fiction (not fantasy), what else could explain the bones? <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
