<div id="review_21791638" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/21791638" />
    <a title="Hallie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1145657-hallie"><img alt="Hallie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1244842998p2/1145657.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/21791638?book_show_action=true">May 07, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hallie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hallie" href="/user/show/1145657-hallie">Hallie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140349122" href="/book/show/831578.The_Perilous_Gard">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1145657-hallie?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1145657-hallie?shelf=ya">ya</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1145657-hallie?shelf=all-time-favourites">all-time-favourites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1145657-hallie?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1145657-hallie?shelf=history-project">history-project</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1145657-hallie?shelf=tam-lin-based-stories">tam-lin-based-stories</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer21791638" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4959315816221632617">This is one of the most often re-read books in our house - definitely the one I read to the daughters the greatest number of times. And with good reason, as it&apos;s fantastic. First there&apos;s the Tam Lin element, which is used beautifully here. Then there&apos;s some of the best dialogue ever (&apos;You don&apos;t look like any god to me, Christopher Heron. You look like a piece of gilded gingerbread.&apos;) And Kate&apos;s a wonderful heroine - intelligent, stubborn when it&apos;s about doing what she feels she should (or not ta</span>
  <span id="freeText4959315816221632617" style="display:none">This is one of the most often re-read books in our house - definitely the one I read to the daughters the greatest number of times. And with good reason, as it's fantastic. First there's the Tam Lin element, which is used beautifully here. Then there's some of the best dialogue ever ('You don't look like any god to me, Christopher Heron. You look like a piece of gilded gingerbread.') And Kate's a wonderful heroine - intelligent, stubborn when it's about doing what she feels she should (or not taking the easy way out) and interesting, rather than beautiful and not much more. And the Faerie (or are they? There's just a hint of doubt about who they are that sets the story off perfectly) are so subtly drawn. And finally, in Christopher, the wounded, arrogant-acting-but-suffering hero is both portrayed to great effect and constantly deflated by Kate's common-sense. </span>
  <a data-text-id="4959315816221632617" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review21791638">
