<span id="freeTextContainer10656909255219865954">What could not be said about this fabulous book?!?!?! I love it!!! One of the few books (along with Jane Austen&apos;s and the Bronte&apos;s) that I read over and over. It perfectly entwines historical fiction with the lore of the fairy folk in a completely believable manner. I really like how the fairy folk were kept true to the old legends and poems of them being sinister and evil. I also loved the herione, she&apos;s great; I hate when the main character is an idiot. And the love story is fabulous. Why don&apos;</span>
  <span id="freeText10656909255219865954" style="display:none">What could not be said about this fabulous book?!?!?! I love it!!! One of the few books (along with Jane Austen's and the Bronte's) that I read over and over. It perfectly entwines historical fiction with the lore of the fairy folk in a completely believable manner. I really like how the fairy folk were kept true to the old legends and poems of them being sinister and evil. I also loved the herione, she's great; I hate when the main character is an idiot. And the love story is fabulous. Why don't more people read this?!? </span>
